      <h1 class='title'>Chips for Everything: Follow-up Report</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 05 February 2004 vol 656 c30WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_30ws' title='Col. 30WS &mdash; HL Deb 05 February 2004 vol 656 c30WS' name='column_30ws' href='#column_30ws' rel='bookmark'>30WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0656P0-06603'>
        <a name='S5LV0656P0_20040205_LWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-sainsbury' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0656P0_20040205_LWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Sainsbury' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-sainsbury" title="Mr David Sainsbury">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, Department of Trade and Industry (Lord Sainsbury of Turville)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0656P0-06603">The Government welcome the follow-up report and recognise the importance of system on chip design to the UK. The main recommendation of the follow-up report&#x2014;the establishment of a managed network&#x2014;aligns well with one of the conclusions of the DTI's innovation review. The Government are supportive of initiatives to set up such a network and have asked Sir Robin Saxby to lead a pilot network in one application area. This will allow key stakeholders to learn how to manage a network of this sort to best effect before committing to something more comprehensive.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
